Start/Create a virtual env:
pipenv shell

Exit from virtual machine:
exit

install django:
pipenv install django

Create Django project:
django-admin startproject myproject

Create new application inside a project:
python manage.py startapp myapp

Run:
python manage.py runserver

After creating new application register that in settings.py inside the project as myapp.app.{Classname}

view.py:  code for each endpoints
create a urls.py inside the application, this is where you define path of each endpoints
register this urls.py in the project's urls.py

models.py:  describe your database schema/model here

python manage.py makemigrations

python manage.py migrate

open shell:
python manage.py shell


Accessing Admin:
Register the models in admin.py
create super user: python manage.py createsuperuser
